(RELIABLE RAG PLATFORM DEMO HANDBOOK) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(Document Purpose) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(This handbook is a sample document created for testing the Reliable RAG Platform. It) Tj
T*
(contains clear facts, dates, module names, constraints, and project decisions so that) Tj
T*
(retrieval, citation generation, and refusal behaviour can be demonstrated during a final) Tj
T*
(year project presentation.) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(The document describes a fictional deployment of the Reliable RAG Platform for an) Tj
T*
(academic document intelligence use case. It is not an official policy document. It is) Tj
T*
(designed only for local testing and public demo purposes.) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(Project Overview) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(The Reliable RAG Platform is a web application that helps users ask questions over) Tj
T*
(uploaded documents. The system combines a FastAPI backend, a React TypeScript frontend,) Tj
T*
(document parsing, chunking, retrieval, Gemini-based answer generation, citation display,) Tj
T*
(and audit logging.) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(The main goal is to reduce hallucination by forcing the answer generator to use only) Tj
T*
(retrieved evidence from the uploaded corpus. If the platform cannot find enough) Tj
T*
(supporting evidence, the system should reply with the exact refusal sentence: "Not found) Tj
T*
(in the provided documents.") Tj
T*
T*
T*
(The application was built as an additional final year project by Lakshit Tandon,) Tj
T*
(registration number 220905506, under the internal guidance of Manjula K. Shenoy.) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(Supported File Types) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(Version 1 of the platform supports PDF, TXT, and Markdown files. The maximum file size) Tj
T*
(for upload is 10 MB. Files larger than this should be rejected before indexing to) Tj
T*
(prevent slow uploads and poor demo performance.) Tj
ET
