T*
T*
(The system supports text-based PDFs. Scanned PDFs and image-only documents are not) Tj
T*
(supported in version 1 because they require OCR. OCR support is planned as future work.) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(Ingestion Pipeline) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(When a user uploads a document, the backend stores the file, calculates a SHA-256) Tj
T*
(checksum, checks for duplicate content, extracts text, splits the text into chunks, and) Tj
T*
(attaches metadata to every chunk.) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(Each chunk stores the document name, document id, page number, section title, chunk) Tj
T*
(text, token count, and source path. This metadata is important because the frontend uses) Tj
T*
(it to show citations and source information.) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(Upload processing runs asynchronously. This means the user can upload a file and the) Tj
T*
(backend can index it in the background while the frontend shows the document status as) Tj
T*
(processing, indexed, or failed.) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(Retrieval Pipeline) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(The query pipeline receives a user question and searches the indexed chunks. The) Tj
T*
(prototype uses lexical retrieval and embedding-style scoring concepts to identify) Tj
T*
(relevant text. The original project plan included Qdrant for dense vectors and Whoosh) Tj
T*
(for BM25 keyword retrieval.) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(The intended production retrieval flow is hybrid retrieval. First, dense retrieval finds) Tj
T*
(semantically similar chunks. Second, BM25 finds keyword-matching chunks. Third,) Tj
T*
(Reciprocal Rank Fusion combines both ranked lists. Fourth, a reranking step selects the) Tj
T*
(strongest evidence chunks. Finally, only the top evidence chunks are passed to the) Tj
T*
(answer generator.) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(The answer generator must not answer from memory. It should answer only from retrieved) Tj
T*
(chunks. This design makes the system more trustworthy than a plain chatbot because every) Tj
ET
