(answer can be traced back to document evidence.) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(Answer Generation Rules) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(The assistant should provide direct answers when evidence is present in the uploaded) Tj
T*
(documents. Every factual answer should include citations. A citation should mention the) Tj
T*
(document name, page number, and section when available.) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(If retrieved evidence is weak, unrelated, or missing, the assistant should refuse) Tj
T*
(instead of guessing. The required refusal message is: "Not found in the provided) Tj
T*
(documents.") Tj
T*
T*
T*
(The platform should not invent missing values. For example, if the documents do not) Tj
T*
(mention a project budget, project marks, production users, or cloud database) Tj
T*
(credentials, the assistant should not create those details.) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(Frontend Modules) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(The frontend contains a corpus dashboard, a query studio, and an audit trail screen. The) Tj
T*
(corpus dashboard is used for uploading, viewing, and deleting documents. The query) Tj
T*
(studio is used for asking questions and viewing citations. The audit trail is used to) Tj
T*
(show important system events such as uploads, deletions, and queries.) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(The login screen is currently simplified for demo use. Full registration, role-based) Tj
T*
(authentication, and profile management are planned as future work.) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(The document preview and metadata panel are also planned as future work. This feature) Tj
T*
(would allow users to open a document, inspect extracted sections, and verify which) Tj
T*
(chunks were used for an answer.) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(Backend Modules) Tj
T*
T*
