(The backend is implemented as a modular monolith. The main modules are API routes,) Tj
T*
(schemas, domain types, storage service, parsing service, chunking service, retrieval) Tj
T*
(service, model service, security helpers, and configuration.) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(FastAPI is used because it provides clean REST APIs, automatic validation through) Tj
T*
(Pydantic models, interactive API documentation, and good support for asynchronous) Tj
T*
(request handling.) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(The backend currently uses in-memory storage for the demo. A persistent PostgreSQL) Tj
T*
(database and durable file storage layer are planned as future work so that uploaded) Tj
T*
(documents and audit logs survive server restarts.) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(Model Integration) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(The project includes a provider-aware model layer. Gemini 2.5 Flash Lite is used for) Tj
T*
(answer generation in the deployed prototype because it has a free-tier option and is) Tj
T*
(suitable for lightweight demonstrations.) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(The system is designed so that the model provider can be changed later without rewriting) Tj
T*
(the entire application. In the future, OpenAI, Gemini, or local models could be plugged) Tj
T*
(into the same query pipeline.) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(Deployment Notes) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(The application is deployed on Render at the public URL https://reliable-rag-) Tj
T*
(platform.onrender.com. The deployment uses Docker so that backend and frontend assets) Tj
T*
(can be built in a repeatable way.) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(For a final year demo, the recommended steps are to upload this handbook, wait for) Tj
T*
(indexing to complete, ask two or three factual questions, inspect citations, ask one) Tj
T*
(negative question, and then show the audit trail.) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(Recommended Demo Questions) Tj
ET
